Build Your Knowledge Base in Salesforce Classic

Create a library of knowledge articles in Salesforce Classic. Assign Knowledge User licenses to yourself and your team.

Salesforce Knowledge is available in the Unlimited Edition with Service Cloud, and for an additional cost in Professional, Enterprise, Performance, and Developer Editions.

To enable Salesforce Knowledge: Customize Application

Plan Your Knowledge Base
Consider your company's needs when developing a strategy for capturing and publishing support expertise. A robust knowledge base helps customers receive service faster or solve their own issues.

Knowledge Article Types
Article types provide the format and structure to control how an article displays for each audience, known as a channel. You can create custom fields, customize the layout, choose a template for each channel, and set up workflow rules and approval processes.

Classic Knowledge User Access
Specify which agents are Classic Knowledge users and give them access to article actions. Create user profiles with needed permissions and assign them to these profiles.

Set Up the Knowledge One Widget
Knowledge One is available as a widget that you can plug in to the Salesforce Console for Service or Salesforce Console for Sales. You can search, send, and create articles without leaving the case.

Articles or Knowledge Tab
Find out which Salesforce Knowledge tab you are using and what you can do on each.

Example Apex for Submitting Articles from Cases
Use Apex to pre-populate fields on draft articles when customer-support agents create them while closing a case.

Use Videos from Any Provider with a Custom Visualforce Page
Insert videos from any provider into your Salesforce Knowledge articles using a custom Visualforce page and the HTML editor.
title: Setting Up Salesforce Knowledge in Classic
